Synopsis:
   $fmtfsize(<bytes>)

Description:
   Converts an integer representing an arbitrary number of bytes into a
   more human readable form.

Returns:
   The file size formatted as bytes, kilobytes, megabytes, gigabytes,
   or terabytes with decimals truncated to 2 digits.

Examples:
   $fmtfsize(1234)                           returns "1.21kb"
   $fmtfsize(12345)                          returns "12.06kb"
   $fmtfsize(123456789)                      returns "117.74mb"

Credits:
   This function was written by wd for the 'mail' script included with EPIC4.

See Also:
   fsize(6)

